{
  "texts": [
    "To detect adversarial attacks based on queries, the produced hash sequence is then compared with those from earlier questions.",
    "Moreover, the goal of the study described by Li et al. [81] was to introduce a new defensive strategy known as robust training (RT).",
    "This approach aims to minimize both the robust risk and standard risk simultaneously.",
    "Furthermore, the scope of RT was expanded to a semisupervised mode to bolster adversarial robustness.",
    "This extension, SRT, proved effective since the robust risk is unrelated to the true label, and the previously p-bounded neighborhood was broadened to encompass various perturbation types."
  ]
}